MONGO_USERNAME=EnterYourUserNameHere
MONGO_PASSWORD=EnterYourPasswordHere

# .gitignore is leaving this out of github commits, so you can just save a copy of your ".env" on your local repository. If you see this file listed as a change on git, then just remove it before committing any changes.

# If you do not have a Database User Id and Password you can create one.
#   1. On the left side under Security, click Database & Network Access
#   2. Go ahead and click the Green "ADD NEW DATABASE USER"
#   3. Authentication method = password, enter username, autogenerate secure password, built in role = atlas admin... blah blah blah....
#   4. IMPORTANT!!! Before you click that Green "Add User" button, make sure you copy and paste your username and password into your personal .env file